890 elements in the stack, and YYPTR gives the new location of the

2046 int yyi;
2047 YYFPRINTF (stderr, "Reducing stack by rule %d (line %lu):\n",

2067/* Nonzero means print parse trace. It is left uninitialized so that
2068 multiple parsers can coexist. */
2069int yydebug;
2070#else /* !YYDEBUG */

2078/* YYINITDEPTH -- initial size of the parser's stacks. */
2079#ifndef YYINITDEPTH
2080# define YYINITDEPTH 200

2083/* YYMAXDEPTH -- maximum size the stacks can grow to (effective only
2084 if the built-in stack extension method is used).
2085
2086 Do not make this value too large; the results are undefined if
2087 YYSTACK_ALLOC_MAXIMUM < YYSTACK_BYTES (YYMAXDEPTH)
2088 evaluated with infinite-precision integer arithmetic. */

2095#if YYERROR_VERBOSE
2096
2097# ifndef yystrlen
2098# if defined __GLIBC__ && defined _STRING_H
2099# define yystrlen strlen
2100# else
2101/* Return the length of YYSTR. */
2102static YYSIZE_T
2103yystrlen (const char *yystr)
2104{
2105 YYSIZE_T yylen;
2106 for (yylen = 0; yystr[yylen]; yylen++)
2107 continue;
2108 return yylen;
2109}
2110# endif
2111# endif
2112
2113# ifndef yystpcpy
2114# if defined __GLIBC__ && defined _STRING_H && defined _GNU_SOURCE
2115# define yystpcpy stpcpy
2116# else
2117/* Copy YYSRC to YYDEST, returning the address of the terminating '\0' in
2118 YYDEST. */
2119static char *
2120yystpcpy (char *yydest, const char *yysrc)
2121{
2122 char *yyd = yydest;
2123 const char *yys = yysrc;
2124
2125 while ((*yyd++ = *yys++) != '\0')
2126 continue;
2127
2128 return yyd - 1;
2129}
2130# endif
2131# endif
2132
2133# ifndef yytnamerr
2134/* Copy to YYRES the contents of YYSTR after stripping away unnecessary
2135 quotes and backslashes, so that it's suitable for yyerror. The
2136 heuristic is that double-quoting is unnecessary unless the string
2137 contains an apostrophe, a comma, or backslash (other than
2138 backslash-backslash). YYSTR is taken from yytname. If YYRES is
2139 null, do not copy; instead, return the length of what the result
2140 would have been. */
2141static YYSIZE_T
2142yytnamerr (char *yyres, const char *yystr)
2143{
2144 if (*yystr == '"')
2145 {
2146 YYSIZE_T yyn = 0;
2147 char const *yyp = yystr;
2148
2149 for (;;)
2150 switch (*++yyp)
2151 {
2152 case '\'':
2153 case ',':
2154 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
2155
2156 case '\\':
2157 if (*++yyp != '\\')
2158 goto do_not_strip_quotes;
2159 /* Fall through. */
2160 default:
2161 if (yyres)
2162 yyres[yyn] = *yyp;
2163 yyn++;
2164 break;
2165
2166 case '"':
2167 if (yyres)
2168 yyres[yyn] = '\0';
2169 return yyn;
2170 }
2171 do_not_strip_quotes: ;
2172 }
2173
2174 if (! yyres)
2175 return yystrlen (yystr);
2176
2177 return yystpcpy (yyres, yystr) - yyres;
2178}
2179# endif
2180
2181/* Copy into *YYMSG, which is of size *YYMSG_ALLOC, an error message
2182 about the unexpected token YYTOKEN for the state stack whose top is
2183 YYSSP.
2184
2185 Return 0 if *YYMSG was successfully written. Return 1 if *YYMSG is
2186 not large enough to hold the message. In that case, also set
2187 *YYMSG_ALLOC to the required number of bytes. Return 2 if the
2188 required number of bytes is too large to store. */
2189static int
2190yysyntax_error (YYSIZE_T *yymsg_alloc, char **yymsg,
2191 yytype_int16 *yyssp, int yytoken)
2192{
2193 YYSIZE_T yysize0 = yytnamerr (YY_NULLPTR, yytname[yytoken]);
2194 YYSIZE_T yysize = yysize0;
2195 enum { YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM = 5 };
2196 /* Internationalized format string. */
2197 const char *yyformat = YY_NULLPTR;
2198 /* Arguments of yyformat. */
2199 char const *yyarg[YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM];
2200 /* Number of reported tokens (one for the "unexpected", one per
2201 "expected"). */
2202 int yycount = 0;
2203
2204 /* There are many possibilities here to consider:
2205 - If this state is a consistent state with a default action, then
2206 the only way this function was invoked is if the default action
2207 is an error action. In that case, don't check for expected
2208 tokens because there are none.
2209 - The only way there can be no lookahead present (in yychar) is if
2210 this state is a consistent state with a default action. Thus,
2211 detecting the absence of a lookahead is sufficient to determine
2212 that there is no unexpected or expected token to report. In that
2213 case, just report a simple "syntax error".
2214 - Don't assume there isn't a lookahead just because this state is a
2215 consistent state with a default action. There might have been a
2216 previous inconsistent state, consistent state with a non-default
2217 action, or user semantic action that manipulated yychar.
2218 - Of course, the expected token list depends on states to have
2219 correct lookahead information, and it depends on the parser not
2220 to perform extra reductions after fetching a lookahead from the
2221 scanner and before detecting a syntax error. Thus, state merging
2222 (from LALR or IELR) and default reductions corrupt the expected
2223 token list. However, the list is correct for canonical LR with
2224 one exception: it will still contain any token that will not be
2225 accepted due to an error action in a later state.
2226 */
2227 if (yytoken != YYEMPTY)
2228 {
2229 int yyn = yypact[*yyssp];
2230 yyarg[yycount++] = yytname[yytoken];
2231 if (!yypact_value_is_default (yyn))
2232 {
2233 /* Start YYX at -YYN if negative to avoid negative indexes in
2234 YYCHECK. In other words, skip the first -YYN actions for
2235 this state because they are default actions. */
2236 int yyxbegin = yyn < 0 ? -yyn : 0;
2237 /* Stay within bounds of both yycheck and yytname. */
2238 int yychecklim = YYLAST - yyn + 1;
2239 int yyxend = yychecklim < YYNTOKENS ? yychecklim : YYNTOKENS;
2240 int yyx;
2241
2242 for (yyx = yyxbegin; yyx < yyxend; ++yyx)
2243 if (yycheck[yyx + yyn] == yyx && yyx != YYTERROR
2244 && !yytable_value_is_error (yytable[yyx + yyn]))
2245 {
2246 if (yycount == YYERROR_VERBOSE_ARGS_MAXIMUM)
2247 {
2248 yycount = 1;
2249 yysize = yysize0;
2250 break;
2251 }
2252 yyarg[yycount++] = yytname[yyx];
2253 {
